  <h4 class="pHead4" >
</h4>    

<a name="wp3696278"> </a><h3 class="pHead3" >
Description
</h3>    

<a name="wp3696279"> </a><p class="pBody" >
The <code class="cCodeBody">assert_even_parity</code> assertion checker checks the expression <span style="font-style: oblique" class="cCodeBodyEmphasis">test_expr</span> at each rising edge of <span style="font-style: oblique" class="cCodeBodyEmphasis">clk</span> to verify the expression evaluates to a value that has even parity. A value has even parity if it is 0 or if the number of bits set to 1 is even.
</p>    
<a name="wp3696281"> </a><p class="pBody" >
The checker is useful for verifying control circuits, for example, it can be used to verify a finite-state machine with error detection. In a datapath circuit the checker can perform parity error checking of address and data buses.
</p>    
<a name="wp3696289"> </a><h4 class="pHead4" >
Assertion Check  </h4>    <div align="left" class="tbl">
<table border="0">
  <caption></caption>
  <tr align="left" valign="top">    <td><a name="wp3696284"> </a><div class="pCellBodyLeft" >
&#160;
</div>    
</td>
    <td><a name="wp3696286"> </a><div class="pCellBodyLeft" >
ASSERT_EVEN_PARITY
</div>    
</td>
    <td><a name="wp3696288"> </a><div class="pCellBodyLeft" >
Expression evaluated to a value whose parity is not even.
</div>    
</td>
</tr>
</table>
</div>
	
